        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1746379809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Ring.KrullDimLE</code> is new. <code>Ring.DimensionLEOne</code> should be replaced by it IMO.</p>",
        "id": 516054812,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1746383239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Because <code>Ring.DimensionLEOne</code> is very wrong. See <a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Dedekind.20ring/near/490122763\">#mathlib4 &gt; Dedekind ring @ üí¨</a></p>",
        "id": 516054927,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1746383306
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"439483\">Andrew Yang</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Finiteness.20of.20residue.20fields.20for.20number.20fields/near/516054927\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>is very wrong</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>... same as <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsDedekindDomain.HeightOneSpectrum#doc\">docs#IsDedekindDomain.HeightOneSpectrum</a> which is in fact non-zero prime ideals, hence wrong for non-Dedekind rings</p>",
        "id": 516080437,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1746403262
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Finiteness.20of.20residue.20fields.20for.20number.20fields/near/515159940\">ÂèëË®ÄÈÅì</a>Ôºö</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We have finiteness of the class group of a number field but I can't find finiteness of the residue fields, which is much easier! Furthermore I am not entirely sure whether I should be just proving it for the ring of integers (approach 2) or more generally (approach 1). Do we have any of these?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think we proved</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ideal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ùìû</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hI</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚â†</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">ùìû</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚ß∏</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>in a previous <a href=\"https://github.com/mbkybky/GaloisRamification/blob/4b4b051ca232bb02f99752fc75bdd4ff1799f81f/GaloisRamification/ToMathlib/Finite.lean#L74\">project</a>.</p>",
        "id": 516095729,
        "sender_full_name": "Yongle Hu",
        "timestamp": 1746413504
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I think this is the same as the proof using <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Ideal.finiteQuotientOfFreeOfNeBot#doc\">docs#Ideal.finiteQuotientOfFreeOfNeBot</a> that <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"439483\">@Andrew Yang</span>  pointed out earlier.</p>",
